            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Depends on the UI (or your terminal).\r\n\r\nThis is somewhat possible already by sending a `busy_start` event from the UI, see `:help ui-global`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n[\"busy_start\"]  \r\n[\"busy_stop\"]  \r\n\tIndicates to the UI that it must stop rendering the cursor. This event\r\n\tis misnamed and does not actually have anything to do with busyness.\r\n```",
